WEBVTT

00:11.970 --> 00:15.849
<i>I was naked, terrified and confused.</i>

00:16.058 --> 00:18.310
<i>How could I have had sex with a man?</i>

00:18.393 --> 00:21.104
<i>And Bob "Boy Crazy" Barnard!</i>

00:21.605 --> 00:27.486
<i>With his perfect man beard and his perfect
man chest and his perfect man arms.</i>

00:29.488 --> 00:31.615
<i>I'd always admired women's things.</i>

00:31.698 --> 00:34.034
<i>Did I desire men's things, too?</i>

00:34.117 --> 00:37.079
<i>Had I been lying to myself my entire life?</i>

00:37.162 --> 00:39.581
<i>I needed time to think, alone.</i>

00:47.047 --> 00:48.757
Fleeing the scene of the crime?

00:49.007 --> 00:51.176
No, I'm just late for work.

00:51.385 --> 00:53.804
Something tells me
your boss will understand.

00:54.763 --> 00:58.225
- Come here.
- Last night was an anomaly, an aberration.

00:58.308 --> 01:01.895
Look, Bob, I get it.
You're scared, ashamed, confused.

01:01.979 --> 01:04.982
Hell, I felt that way the first
eight or nine times I had gay sex.

01:05.274 --> 01:06.984
Could we please not call it that?

01:07.067 --> 01:10.779
All I'm saying is, if anyone understands
what you're going through, it's me.

01:11.446 --> 01:15.075
It doesn't mean last night was a mistake.
I told you, I love you.

01:15.158 --> 01:16.827
Stop, okay?

01:16.910 --> 01:20.122
Coralee and I have been
going to therapy for weeks,

01:20.205 --> 01:22.916
trying to work it out,
and we are really making progress.

01:23.166 --> 01:26.378
And yet you found yourself
on my doorstep last night. Why?

01:26.461 --> 01:28.755
Because I couldn't get that kissÂ out
of my head.

01:29.131 --> 01:33.802
And then, when you said that
maybe I'd spent 30 years hating you

01:34.344 --> 01:35.387
because really I was...

01:35.470 --> 01:36.930
Madly in love with me?

01:37.014 --> 01:38.265
Well, I wouldn't go that far.

01:39.266 --> 01:44.438
But I do think that maybe I had feelings
that I needed to explore.

01:45.063 --> 01:46.023
And now?

01:46.106 --> 01:48.900
Now, I have explored them,
and I can move on with my life.

01:54.865 --> 01:56.325
- Stop it.
- Why?

01:56.575 --> 01:57.993
Because I love it!

01:58.076 --> 02:00.495
And I don't know how it fits
into the rest of my life!

02:00.579 --> 02:02.372
All right. I'm sorry.

02:03.790 --> 02:06.877
I remember being where you are.
You just... you need time.

02:07.377 --> 02:12.424
I just hope we can keep seeing
each other while you figure it out.

02:12.674 --> 02:14.384
How? I have a wife.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.552
I do too.

02:16.136 --> 02:18.263
I love Etta Mae and Magnolia,

02:18.347 --> 02:20.349
but what they don't know can't hurt them.

02:20.432 --> 02:22.017
But you are lying to them.

02:22.100 --> 02:23.602
It's better than lying to myself,

02:23.935 --> 02:27.898
trying to convince myself
I felt fulfilled when I wasn't.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.316
So, what do I do?

02:29.691 --> 02:32.069
You got to do what I do.
You compartmentalize.

02:32.152 --> 02:35.072
You keep this and Coralee separate.

